                      .----------------------------------.
                      |       Installation aMI-hELP      |
                      `----------------------------------'

              aMI-hELP  can  be installed like any /X 3.x+ command.

                              copy ram:bbs/#? bbs:

                 assuming You have unpacked the archive to ram:

@ENDNODE

@NODE AmiUsage "Usage in Ami-Express - © 1996 tRESPASS/mYSTiC"
                          .------------------------.
                          |  Usage in Ami-Express  |
                          `------------------------'

  To start Ami-Help from the bbs command line type h or Help and press
  return. this will give you a menu looking similar to a bbs main menu
  the greatness here is that now you can choose your command.

      [G] for example and the follwing will pop up on the screen 

                       cOMMAND [G] - Goodbye/Logoff

          this will be followed by a descriptve summary of the command
          [G] and what it does. EG: Files still flagged etc etc!

     This way Your users are not getting confused about flagged files!!!

@ENDNODE

